A suspected thug was on Thursday night shot dead by police and a pistol loaded with five bullets recovered. His accomplice managed to escape and is being pursued by police. Officers from the special crime prevention unit ambushed the suspects at the Muthaiga bridge. The two men were riding on a motorbike. They are said to have been headed to the city centre for a robbery mission. The incident happened at 11.30 pm. Click here for the latest political news 